## Integration steps

### 1. Add files to your project

Copy the `edgeforge_output/` directory into your firmware project, then:

**CMakeLists.txt:**
```cmake
add_subdirectory(edgeforge_output)
target_link_libraries(${PROJECT_NAME} edgeforge_{{ info.model_name }})
```

**Or manually add sources:**
```cmake
target_sources(${PROJECT_NAME} PRIVATE
    edgeforge_output/model.c
    edgeforge_output/inference_runner.c
{% if rtos != "none" %}    edgeforge_output/rtos_glue.c
{% endif %})
target_include_directories(${PROJECT_NAME} PRIVATE edgeforge_output/)
```

### 2. Add TFLite Micro dependency

EdgeForge generates code targeting the TFLite Micro runtime.
Add it to your project following the [TFLite Micro setup guide](https://github.com/tensorflow/tflite-micro).

### 3. Call from your firmware

```c
#include "inference_runner.h"

static edgeforge_model_t model;
static edgeforge_input_t  input_buf[EDGEFORGE_INPUT_SIZE  / sizeof(edgeforge_input_t)];
static edgeforge_output_t output_buf[EDGEFORGE_OUTPUT_SIZE / sizeof(edgeforge_output_t)];

void app_init(void) {
    edgeforge_status_t status = edgeforge_init(&model);
    if (status != EDGEFORGE_OK) {
        /* Handle init failure */
    }
}

void on_sensor_data_ready(void) {
    /* Fill input_buf with preprocessed sensor data */
    /* Shape: [{{ info.input.shape_str }}]  Type: {{ info.input.c_type }} */

    edgeforge_status_t status = edgeforge_infer(&model, input_buf, output_buf);
    if (status == EDGEFORGE_OK) {
        /* Read results from output_buf */
        /* Shape: [{{ info.output.shape_str }}]  Type: {{ info.output.c_type }} */
    }
}
```

